went immediately to our Rooms Friday
bought in Holland many years ago
was quite comforted at ye . sight of her fine boy . -- This is her 6 th . Son -- she never had a Girl -- she has now
Went to our Rooms soon after 11 -- Saturday
August 1784 Dreſs 'd at 7 for ye . day at 8 went
wrote ye . first letter to me yesterday
died when she was very Young She is near a Year
was suitably married to a Gentleman of good fortune . it was a match of inclination & they were mutually happy , a few short years
went to my Room at 12 . Sunday
goes into Devonshire in a few days
Wednesday Morn.g . Mrs. Vesey . Handcock & I took
August 1784 -- Dreſs 'd at ½ past7 -- B . in my own Room Mr. Saunders Ye . Painter came
May 1785 , I should have when I chose
married -- she has been wth .. her 26 or 7 Years
put of her Journey till ye . next day
believe more , of our intimates who were of my age were dead in ye . space of 9 Years
had seen Mrs. Walsingham & Miſs Boyle yesterday
Recd . a good Acct . of Lady Stormont & her little boy . Wednesday
August 1784 Dreſs 'd before 8 for ye . day . breakfasted
staid in Town wch . is till Saturday
went to our Rooms -- rec 'd very good accounts of Lady Stormont & ye . Child 12 August
told me that she was at Chelsea Yesterday
Friday Breakfasted wth . Anna Maria -- at 10 oClock dreſs 'd for ye . day . at 11 Miſs Murray came
work 'd the debates in ye . House of Lords yesterday
10 Years old a pretty unaffected child . her genius for Music is astonishing -- she does not practise
1784 Dreſs 'd at ½ past 7 for ye . day -- Work 'd notable work -- B in my Own Room -- Recd . a letter from Windsor -- written
dyed my Cheeks by warm Congratulations & wishes -- he had been at Windsor yesterday
a Month there . & that in ye . mean
found her pretty well after her little excursion of yesterday
wch . her friend ye . Dſs . had turn 'd for her some Years
Tuesday next a M rs came
went to our Room immediately -- My Uncle Fredk_ Mrs . & Miſs Hamilton had call 'd in ye . Morng . Monday
a day with her at her Villa . After ye . Dſs . & her Mother was gone
tomorrow as she was apprehensive of ye . great heat of ye . Weather . I left
August . At 8 o'Clock Dreſs 'd for ye . day . went
abt our expedition to Ken Wood next Sunday
left us -- some more Matches were talk 'd of -- Miſs Woodley to be marri d e d tomorrow
